default  These show, for those aged 25 to 49, the importance of driving a car outside of London, and particul
defaultarly in rural areas, and the relatively little use of buses outside London and the metropolitan conurbations.  For those aged 65 to 69, driving a car is still important, but fewer journeys are as a car driver; bus use in urban (population 25,000 to 250,000
default) and small urban areas increases relative to that by middle-aged people.  For those aged 80 and over, the total number of journeys has reduced considerably
default, and car driving in particular. 
default 
defaultJourneys as a car driver are still more in rural than urban areas,
